member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_REFRESH
member.summary: Asks the receiver to refresh its display. Implemented by the document/object.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_STOP
member.summary: Stops all current processing. Implemented by the document/object.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_HIDETOOLBARS
member.summary: View menu, Toolbars command. Implemented by the document/object to hide its toolbars.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETPROGRESSMAX
member.summary: Sets the maximum value of a progress indicator if one is owned by the receiving object, usually a frame. The minimum value is always zero.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETPROGRESSPOS
member.summary: Sets the current value of a progress indicator if one is owned by the receiving object, usually a frame.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETPROGRESSTEXT
member.summary: Sets the text contained in a progress indicator if one is owned by the receiving object, usually a frame. If the receiver currently has no progress indicator, this text should be displayed in the status bar (if one exists) as with .

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETTITLE
member.summary: Sets the title bar text of the receiving object, usually a frame.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETDOWNLOADSTATE
member.summary: Called by the object when downloading state changes. Takes a VT_BOOL parameter, which is TRUE if the object is downloading data and FALSE if it not. Primarily implemented by the frame.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_STOPDOWNLOAD
member.summary: Stops the download when executed. Typically, this command is propagated to all contained objects. When queried, sets MSOCMDF_ENABLED. Implemented by the document/object.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_FIND
member.summary: Edit menu, Find command

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_DELETE
member.summary: Edit menu, Delete command

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_HTTPEQUIV
member.summary: Issued in response to HTTP-EQUIV metatag and results in a call to the deprecated method with the fDone parameter set to false. This command takes a VT_BSTR parameter which is passed to OnHttpEquiv.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_HTTPEQUIV_DONE
member.summary: Issued in response to HTTP-EQUIV metatag and results in a call to the deprecated method with the fDone parameter set to true. This command takes a VT_BSTR parameter which is passed to OnHttpEquiv.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_ENABLE_INTERACTION
member.summary: Pauses or resumes receiver interaction. This command takes a VT_BOOL parameter that pauses interaction when set to FALSE and resumes interaction when set to TRUE.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_ONUNLOAD
member.summary: Notifies the receiver of an intent to close the window imminently. This command takes a VT_BOOL output parameter that returns TRUE if the receiver can close and FALSE if it can't.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_PROPERTYBAG2

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_PREREFRESH

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SETPRINTTEMPLATE
member.summary: Sets an explicit Print Template value of TRUE or FALSE, based on a VT_BOOL input parameter.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_GETPRINTTEMPLATE
member.summary: Gets a VT_BOOL output parameter indicating whether the Print Template value is TRUE or FALSE.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_PAGEACTIONBLOCKED
member.summary: Indicates that a page action has been blocked. PAGEACTIONBLOCKED is designed for use with applications that host the Internet Explorer WebBrowser control to implement their own UI.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_PAGEACTIONUIQUERY
member.summary: Specifies which actions are displayed in the Internet Explorer notification band.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_FOCUSVIEWCONTROLS
member.summary: Causes the Internet Explorer WebBrowser control to focus its default notification band. Hosts can send this command at any time. The return value is S_OK if the band is present and is in focus, or S_FALSE otherwise.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_FOCUSVIEWCONTROLSQUERY
member.summary: This notification event is provided for applications that display Internet Explorers default notification band implementation. By default, when the user presses the ALT-N key combination, Internet Explorer treats it as a request to focus the notification band.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_SHOWPAGEACTIONMENU
member.summary: Causes the Internet Explorer WebBrowser control to show the Information Bar menu.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_ADDTRAVELENTRY
member.summary: Causes the Internet Explorer WebBrowser control to create an entry at the current Travel Log offset. The Docobject should implement ITravelLogClient and interfaces, which are used by the Travel Log as it processes this command with calls to GetWindowData and GetPersistID, respectively.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_UPDATETRAVELENTRY
member.summary: Called when LoadHistory is processed to update the previous Docobject state. For synchronous handling, this command can be called before returning from the LoadHistory call. For asynchronous handling, it can be called later.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_UPDATEBACKFORWARDSTATE
member.summary: Updates the state of the browser's Back and Forward buttons.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_OPTICAL_ZOOM
member.summary: Windows Internet Explorer 7 and later. Sets the zoom factor of the browser. Takes a VT_I4 parameter in the range of 10 to 1000 (percent).

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_OPTICAL_GETZOOMRANGE
member.summary: Windows Internet Explorer 7 and later. Retrieves the minimum and maximum browser zoom factor limits. Returns a VT_I4 parameter; the LOWORD is the minimum zoom factor, the HIWORD is the maximum.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_WINDOWSTATECHANGED
member.summary: Windows Internet Explorer 7 and later. Notifies the Internet Explorer WebBrowser control of changes in window states, such as losing focus, or becoming hidden or minimized. The host indicates what has changed by setting OLECMDID_WINDOWSTATE_FLAG option flags in nCmdExecOpt.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_ACTIVEXINSTALLSCOPE
member.summary: Windows Internet Explorer 8 with Windows Vista. Has no effect with Windows Internet Explorer 8 with Windows XP. Notifies Trident to use the indicated Install Scope to install the ActiveX Control specified by the indicated Class ID. For more information, see the Remarks section.

member.name: OLECMDID.OLECMDID_UPDATETRAVELENTRY_DATARECOVERY
member.summary: Internet Explorer 8. Unlike OLECMDID_UPDATETRAVELENTRY, this updates a Travel Log entry that is not initialized from a previous Docobject state. While this command is not called from IPersistHistory.LoadHistory, it can be called separately to save browser state that can be used later to recover from a crash.
